                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <seg type="script">15th-century script.</seg>
                                <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                                <desc>Careful, regular; by a good scribe. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3182ContiRo">Carlo Conti Rossini</persName> describes the handwriting as <cit>
                                        <quote>Crude script. Vulgar forms, for example, Panṭalyon
                                            almost always instead of Panṭalēwon.</quote>
                                    </cit>(<cit>
                                        <quote xml:lang="fr">ʻÉcriture rude. Formes vulgaires, par
                                            exemple Panṭalyon, presque toujours, pour
                                            Panṭalēwon.</quote>
                                    </cit>) <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1071dAbbadi">Antoine d’Abbadie [d’Arrast]</persName> describes the
                                    handwriting as <cit>
                                        <quote>ancient script; arabesques and hieroglyphs.</quote>
                                    </cit>(<cit>
                                        <quote xml:lang="fr">écriture antique; arabesques et
                                            hiéroglyphes.</quote>
                                    </cit>)</desc>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
